Durban - UKZN's Professor Nana Poku has been appointed as the acting Vice-Chancellor at the University of KwaZulu Natal replacing Dr Albert van Jaarsveld. Poku's appointment follows the resignation of  Dr van Jaarsveld in June who takes on a new role of Director General and CEO of the International Institute for Applied Systems Analysis (IISA) in Austria. He spent 3 years at the helm. Poku's who will start on October 1, is currently the Deputy Vice-Chancellor and College Head of Law and Management Studies at the University. Professor Poku’s acting appointment will continue until the process of appointing a new Vice-Chancellor and Principal is concluded the university said in a statement on Wednesday. They added that they had embarked on a recruitment process to fill the position. The Council also expressed its appreciation to Dr van Jaarsveld for his leadership during his tenure, and welcomed Professor Poku to this important responsibility. Daily News.